JC<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujethuj.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jethuj</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/4/02 9:41:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=502.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Yay for Community Spirit</span><hr size=1> First off all P A R O D I E S are exempted from copyright law according to the US Supreme Court (you think Weird Al Yankovic is ever going to be mistaken for Madonna or Rick Moranis for Darth Vador in Space Balls?)  and I don't believe any dunderhead could ever mistaken the Iksar on the FV for the movie characters.   Explain to me how anyone can be offended?  This is an abuse and totally outrageous!  If this is how they go about 'the stated policy' then Verant should be forced to change the name of RiverVale...  I should write Tokkien's Estate and point this out... I remember 20 years ago they went BALLSITIC when TSR called haflings hobbits... The pot calling the kettle black.  <br>
