<br>
I've played this game for quite some time now and I've been known as over 15 names.  So I could absolutely care less if I had to change this one, and that would hold for any of my other names.  In my mind it is far, far better than running around as &quot;Smegma&quot; to a large subset of players!  That's one scarlet letter I'd rather not have on my head, thank you.<br>
<br>
By the way, Smegma and Stumpy are in no way comparible.  Nor are the comparisons to Gay, Dick, or Randy (and yes, in the US we know what Randy means also).<br>
<br>
Smegma: the cheesy sebaceous matter that collects between the glans penis and the foreskin or around the clitoris and labia minora.  (Thanks Mirriam Webster!)Colloqually known as &quot;smeg&quot;<br>
<br>
Stumpy: A nickname, that is not politically correct for someone who has a wooden appendage.<br>
<br>
And you are telling me that &quot;Toodumbtorun&quot; is somehow more petitionable?  OK... And I'm sure that the Erudite I saw running around the other day named &quot;Bignigdik&quot; is peachy also, because for all I know it means &quot;beautiful day&quot; in Swahili and who am I to spoil his fun...  <br>
<br>
Honestly now folks, it seems a bit silly to blast people who petition names; everyone is equally entitled by the $13 to their fun, whether it is running around as ninja turtles on a RP server, or whether it is roleplaying an evil drow out for world domination.  That's why there are GMs, to mediate, and see whether things are in violation of the policies of the game.<br>
<br>
As for Verant's actual level of risk in this situation, that doesn't matter.  It was high enough that they made a naming policy to prevent usage of trademarked name.  The policy is what it is, and as you said yourself Jens, they knew it, they ran the risk, and I'm sure they will still have fun with their new names. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kloevis>Kloevis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 193<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/5/02 1:07:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=502.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.cci.clarku.edu/ebarry/pix.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: I wouldn't care</span><hr size=1> This all boils down to one thing.<br>
