<br>
On OTHER servers, they actually take a fairly lax view of the whole thing, depending on the GM staff.  Since FV is actually billed as the role-play server, the GMs here seem to take VIís stated policy a little more seriously.<br>
<br>
ìThe Turtlesî probably would never have been nixed on, say, Prexus, Iíll wager.  Here, on the server that Verant ostensibly created for the enjoyment of people who like to be a little more fully immersed in the fantasy, they removed what was a pretty obvious parody.<br>
<br>
Again, the person that petitioned did nothing.  The GMs were alerted to the names, evaluated them and decided they violated the policy.  If this (alleged) person had not petitioned now, they would have simply had a stay of execution, not permission to continue.<br>
<br>
There is also the possibility that there is no petitioner.  The GM who changed their name may have just made that up so that he would not have to listen to the turtleís complaints as he implemented Verantís policy.  Unlikely, Iíll grant, since the GMs donít usually have any issue with saying what they mean, but possible.<br>
<br>
Although I would not have petitioned them, I am not sorry to see a reference to a kidís TV show be removed from the game.  I would have the same feelings if Ashkatchum, Peeekichew and Charmannder had their names changed.  Same with the adventuring pair of Megaatron and Optimous.<br>
<br>
I know some people really get joy from making up clever names in-game.  I respect that they do not have the same inclination to actually ëcreate a characterí (as opposed to a ëtooní) in the game as I do.  But in the end, my opinions on names are meaningless: the are rules in the sandbox, and complaining once you finally get caught is just silly.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uakylah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Akylah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/5/02 9:07:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=502.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I wouldn't care</span><hr size=1> Exactly Henk.<br>
<br>
Kloevis, prove that the person who did it is a &quot;RP Nazi&quot;.  The simple truth is that you don't know who did it or why they did it.  Like Henk said, the GM could have just been saying that they received an e-mail, like the turtles said it could have been someone who just didn't like the show. It could have been a non-roleplayer who just thought the names were stupid, and didn't realize they took their names so seriously that petitioning them would cause people to react as if he had hit one of them with a car.  Could have been the trademark holder's lawyer. Could have been some VI employee.  It could have been one of the people on this thread who is mercilessly bashing RPers.  <br>
